comments.body:
Bug: String.prototype.replace() replaces the first occurrence of the substring, not the one at position fullStart. If the sliced content happens to appear earlier in the template, this replaces the wrong part.

Fix: use positional string surgery instead:

  interpolated = interpolated.slice(0, fullStart) + interpolated.slice(fullEnd);

and on line 124:

  interpolated = interpolated.slice(0, fullStart) + blockContent + interpolated.slice(fullEnd);

This faithfully implements the positional intent of the indexOf lookup above.

